  "prompt": "How should I eat in order to both build muscle and lose body fat?",
  "response": "To build muscle and lose body fat simultaneously (often called \"body recomposition\"), follow these dietary guidelines:\n\n1. Protein Intake\n- Consume 1.6-2.2 grams of protein per kg of body weight daily\n- Eat lean protein sources like chicken, fish, lean beef, eggs, and protein supplements\n- Spread protein intake across meals\n\n2. Calorie Management\n- Maintain a slight caloric deficit (10-20% below maintenance calories)\n- Calculate your total daily energy expenditure (TDEE) and adjust accordingly\n- Focus on nutrient-dense, whole foods\n\n3. Macronutrient Balance\n- High protein\n- Moderate complex carbohydrates\n- Healthy fats\n- Aim for roughly:\n  * 40% protein\n  * 30% carbs\n  * 30% fat\n\n4. Meal Timing\n- Eat 4-6 smaller meals per day\n- Consume protein and carbs before and after workouts\n- Stay hydrated\n\n5. Food Choices\n- Whole grains\n- Vegetables\n- Lean proteins\n- Healthy fats (nuts, avocados, olive oil)\n- Minimize processed foods and added sugars\n\n6. Supplement Considerations\n- Whey protein\n- Creatine\n- Multivitamins\n\nCombine this diet with strength training and consistent exercise for best results.",
